Release Notes
============

Version 3.5.0:
* The project is quiet old, but I love it. To keep it in a usable format it is time to make some rough changes (srry Nikolai).
* In my first commits I target 3 issues:
* 1. The editor is just unusable (it does not feature revert, auto-completion, strg+c is insert a c-chord, search & replace for debugging ...)
*   Here I will go with Visual Studio Code, because it is lightweight and platform independent. In comparison to Sublime Text it does have a debugger and no licensing popups.
* 2. The latex side is completely hidden behind a server.
*   I will remove the binding to the server side, which is the biggest differences.  I think most users of this program have already tex installed or are willing o install it for the 
advantages.
* 3. Make it minimal for easy adjustments and better debugging  
*   adding some small features as in tabulature \color \bold \italic support and some adjustments, arrows ...


